The Naiki was independent of the {{ill|Shitōkan|ja|四等官|1=Shitōkan|qq=draft}} hierarchy as a Hinkan (品官) within the Ministry of the Center. Their office, known as the Naiki-kyoku (内記局), was located south of the {{ill|Left Guards' Barracks|ja|左兵衛陣|qq=draft}}. Following the Chinese system of {{ill|Kikyōchu|ja|起居注|qq=draft}}, the Naiki kept daily records of the emperor's activities, compiling them into the "Naiki Nikki" (内記日記). However, due to the aforementioned decline in their role, this practice ceased in the late Heian period, and only fragments of these records remain.

== Personnel ==
* '''Dai Naiki''' (大内記, 正六位上, Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade): Initially 2 positions, later reduced to 1  
* '''Chū Naiki''' (中内記, 正七位上, Senior Seventh Rank, Upper Grade): 2 positions, abolished in {{ill|806|ja|806th year|qq=draft}}  
* '''Shō Naiki''' (少内記, 正八位上, Senior Eighth Rank, Upper Grade): 2 positions, raised to Senior Seventh Rank after the abolition of Chū Naiki  
