However, during the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heian period|qq=}}, the role of the Naiki gradually declined. While their responsibilities included maintaining official records of the emperor's actions, Naiki were prohibited from entering the emperor's private quarters, the {{ill|Dairi|ja|内裏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Dairi|qq=}}. The establishment of the {{ill|Kurododokoro|ja|蔵人所|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurododokoro|qq=}} allowed the {{ill|Kurodo|ja|蔵人|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurodo|qq=}} to access the Dairi, and the emperor began issuing orders ({{ill|Chokushi|ja|勅旨|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chokushi|qq=}}) to the {{ill|Daijō-kan|ja|太政官|1=Daijō-kan|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daijō-kan|13=User:Immanuelle/Daijō-kan|qq=}} through the Kurodo. This reduced the necessity for the emperor to leave the Dairi and consequently diminished contact between the emperor and the Naiki, resulting in the loss of their role in recording the emperor’s actions. Furthermore, the {{ill|Geki|ja|外記|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Geki|qq=}} expanded their influence, taking over the Naiki’s responsibility for drafting imperial edicts. This series of changes ultimately rendered the Naiki’s functions obsolete.

The Naiki was independent of the {{ill|Shitōkan|ja|四等官|1=Shitōkan|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shitōkan|13=User:Immanuelle/Shitōkan|qq=}} hierarchy as a Hinkan (品官) within the Ministry of the Center. Their office, known as the Naiki-kyoku (内記局), was located south of the {{ill|Left Guards' Barracks|ja|左兵衛陣|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Left Guards' Barracks|qq=}}. Following the Chinese system of {{ill|Kikyōchu|ja|起居注|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kikyōchu|qq=}}, the Naiki kept daily records of the emperor's activities, compiling them into the "Naiki Nikki" (内記日記). However, due to the aforementioned decline in their role, this practice ceased in the late Heian period, and only fragments of these records remain.

== Personnel ==
* '''Dai Naiki''' (大内記, 正六位上, Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade): Initially 2 positions, later reduced to 1  
* '''Chū Naiki''' (中内記, 正七位上, Senior Seventh Rank, Upper Grade): 2 positions, abolished in {{ill|806|ja|806年|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/806|qq=}}  
* '''Shō Naiki''' (少内記, 正八位上, Senior Eighth Rank, Upper Grade): 2 positions, raised to Senior Seventh Rank after the abolition of Chū Naiki  
* '''Shisei''' (史生): Replaced Chū Naiki, 4 positions  
